<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12017f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12017f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12017f"> 17(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Abred &mdash; changer ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le sens ordinaire d&apos;<i><mark>abred</mark></i> est celui de <i>mal</i>, et, de ce substantif, d&eacute;rivent <i>abredig</i>, <i>abredawg</i>, mauvais, vil. Mais <i>abrediad</i>, signifie transmigration, <i>abredu</i> transmigrer, et ce sens-l&agrave; nous conduit &agrave; la forme plus simple <i>pred</i>, migration, <i>preidiaw</i>, errer. <br><font color="green">[The usual sense of <i>abred</i> is <i>evil</i> and, from this substantive, <i>abredig</i>, <i>abredawg</i>, bad, vile, are derived. But <i>abrediad</i> means transmigration, <i>abredu</i> to transmigrate, and this particular meaning leads to the most simple form <i>pred</i>, migration, <i>preidiaw</i>, to wander.]</font> <small> Adolphe Pictet, trad.  <a name="APMB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APMB"><cite title="source">Le myst&egrave;re des bardes de l'&icirc;le de Bretagne</cite></a> (1856) 34</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
